  <h1 id="main-heading" style="margin-bottom:20px">What Is Old English? A Complete Guide to Anglo-Saxon Language</h1>
  <p class="serif" style="color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:40px">Old English is one of the oldest forms of the English language, spoken by the Anglo-Saxons from roughly 450 to 1150 AD. It is the direct ancestor of the language spoken by over 1.5 billion people today — yet it is almost unrecognisable to the modern eye.</p>
  <div class="divider"></div>
